Comments:
Not Swabbed, Estimated about 6 dead gulls (herring and ring bill gulls) and 1 very visibly sick gull in a stretch of beach about 100ft long on Green Island (Bay of Islands Region). These observations were made while we were setting up song bird recorders on the beach (QFN) and was only a quick snap shot of what was present as we didn't want to spend more time than necessary in the area. This was also only on a very small portion of the island, so the numbers provided are estimates. Total healthy is just an estimate of gulls in total, there is a whole colony on the island. There are also Cormorants and Guillemonts present.

SiteName: Herring Cove Beach, Champney's Arm, Port Rexton
Comments:
Not Swabbed, Today I saw three dead northern gannet's on the beach in Champney's Arm (Port Rexton, NL), as well as one living gannet on the short that didn't seem well. I saw a second live gannet (that didn't seem in good health) on the side of the road on Robbin Hood Beach (port rexton, NL). Over the last week, I have also seen an increasing number of dead and sick common murres (I will report these in a separate post). I have never previously seen either of these birds on the shore. Here is the exact location: https://www.google.com/maps/place/Champney's+Arm,+Port+Rexton,+NL+A0C+2H0/@48.3871182,-53.317102,16z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x4b74f641e5919bf5:0x7ca8664cf95f4fbe!8m2!3d48.391648!4d-53.3072319.
